# üõ† Tool Installation Guide

This guide explains how to set up the lab environment for the Network & Web Forensics Project.

---

# üñ• Lab Environment

Recommended Setup:

- Host OS: Windows 10 / 11
- Virtualization: VirtualBox or VMware
- Attacker Machine: Kali Linux
- Victim Server: Ubuntu Server (Apache)
- Client Machine: Windows 10

---

# 1Ô∏è‚É£ Install VirtualBox

Download:
https://www.virtualbox.org/

Install normally using default settings.

---

# 2Ô∏è‚É£ Install Kali Linux (Attacker Machine)

Download Kali ISO:
https://www.kali.org/get-kali/

Steps:
1. Create new VM
2. Allocate 4GB RAM (minimum 2GB)
3. 2 CPU cores
4. 40GB disk
5. Install using ISO

---

# 3Ô∏è‚É£ Install Ubuntu Server (Web Server)

Download Ubuntu Server ISO:
https://ubuntu.com/download/server

Create VM:
- 2GB RAM
- 20GB disk


4Ô∏è‚É£ Install Apache Web Server
sudo apt install apache2 -y

Check status:

sudo systemctl status apache2

Enable logs:

Logs are located in:

/var/log/apache2/access.log
/var/log/apache2/error.log
5Ô∏è‚É£ Install Wireshark

On Kali:

sudo apt install wireshark -y

Launch:

wireshark
6Ô∏è‚É£ Install Zeek

On Ubuntu or Kali:

sudo apt install zeek -y

Run analysis on PCAP:

zeek -r capture.pcap

Logs will be generated in current directory.

7Ô∏è‚É£ Install Nmap
sudo apt install nmap -y

Example scan:

nmap -sS <target-ip>
8Ô∏è‚É£ Install SQLMap
sudo apt install sqlmap -y

Example usage:

sqlmap -u "http://target-ip/vulnerable.php?id=1" --dbs
9Ô∏è‚É£ Install Splunk (SIEM)

Download Splunk Enterprise (Trial):
https://www.splunk.com/

On Ubuntu:

sudo dpkg -i splunk_package.deb
sudo /opt/splunk/bin/splunk start

Access Web Interface:

http://localhost:8000
üîü Optional: Install DVWA (Vulnerable Web App)
sudo apt install git -y
cd /var/www/html
sudo git clone https://github.com/digininja/DVWA.git



After installation, update system:

```bash
sudo apt update && sudo apt upgrade -y
